<P>THE Al&s;ufficient Phy&s;ician Tendering to Heal the Political and Spiritual <HI>Wounds</HI> &amp; <HI>Sickne&s;&s;es</HI> OF A Di&s;tre&s;&s;ed PROVINCE.</P>
<P>As it was Di&s;cour&s;ed in a SERMON Preached before His Excellency the GOVERNOUR, the Honourable COUNCIL and Repre&s;entatives of the Province of the <HI>Ma&s;&s;achu&s;etts-Bay</HI> in <HI>New-England,</HI> on <HI>May</HI> 30. 1711.</P>
<P>Which was the Day for Election of Her Maje&s;ties Council for that Province.</P>
<P><HI>By</HI> PETER THACHER, <HI>A. M.</HI> And Pa&s;tor of the Church in <HI>Milton.</HI></P>
